cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with allocation of jobs in geo-distributed cloud networks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers communication constraints among sub-tasks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper deals with graph structures. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes solutions for the NP-hard allocation problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also relevant as the paper deals with the NP-complete sub-graph isomorphism problem.
